Shrimp Mogador with Chermoula
  -- Ben Poremba

Chermoula:
1/3 c chopped cilantro
1/3 c chopped parsley
3 garlic cloves, microplaned
1 tsp cumin
1 tsp freshly grated ginger
1/2 tsp fenugreek
1 c lemon juice
1/3 c olive oil
salt and pepper to taste

Using a mortar and pestle, or food processor, pound or pulse all the ingredients except the lemon juice and olive oil. Slowly add lemon juice and olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Set aside.

Shrimp:
4 c oil (canola, grapeseed, or peanut) for frying
1 lb pound large shrimp - heads removed bodies shelled and deveined
1 c wondra flour
1/2 tsp smoked paprika
1/2 tsp ground coriander
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1 tsp kosher salt
1/2 tsp ground white pepper
5 egg whites
2 tbsp club soda
1 c panko bread crumbs

Heat oil in a dutch oven or deep skillet to 325F. Using a small paring knife, make an incision halfway through at the back of the shrimp lengthwise. Carefully open along the cut seam without removing the tail. Lightly pound the shrimp to flatten it. In a medium bowl mix the flour, spices, salt, and pepper together. In another medium bowl, lightly beat the whites and thing them out with the club soda. Set aside. Dredge each shrimp in the flour mixture, then dip in the egg mixture. repeat, then cover with panko. Either freeze the shrimp, sinfle file, for up to a week, or fry them immediately. Fry in the oil 3 min if unfrozen or ~5 min if frozen, until the shrimp is golden brown. Serve with the chermoula on the side.
